               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371023-name-1258" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1258" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1258" type="surname" value="ADEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1258" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS ADEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an apprentice to Samuel Hagger, a wheelwright, in Fashion-street, Spitalfields. On the 23rd of October the prisoner Tho<lb></lb>mas came, and said he came from Mr. Lewis, and wanted the hire of a truck—my master said he knew his rule was always to leave 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he said he had not got 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., he would leave 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he only wanted it two hours, and that would pay for it—I saw no more of it till the Tuesday morning—I went to make inquiries, and was directed to Tower-street station-house, where I saw the wheels and axletree—they are my master's—I never saw any thing of the prisoner Alfred.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Thomas Neate. Q.</hi> You knew me? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371023-name-1259" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1259" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1259" type="surname" value="MEACOCK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1259" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS MEACOCK</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 23rd of October the prisoners came to my shop with the wheels and axletree, and wanted 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I made in<lb></lb>quiry about whose they were, and their story differed—Thomas said he</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183710230181"></xptr>
               <p>would call a third person, and went off—I said that would not do for me—I went after him, brought him back, and gave him into custody, with the other—he had got 100 yards from my house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371023-name-1260" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1260" type="surname" value="LESLIE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1260" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD LESLIE</persName>
                  </hi>. I took the prisoners, and at the station-house Tho<lb></lb>mas said his brother had bought it for him some time ago, but be found taking things about was no use, and he wanted to sell the truck.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Thomas Neate's Defence.</hi> I went to move some goods for a person—I got 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—the man gave me some drink—I knew my children wanted bread, and a man suggested to me if I went to France I could get employment there—I am a gold-beater by trade—I had but 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and I meant to sell the wheels, and send a letter to the prosecutor to say where the body of it was—my son had nothing to do with it.</p>
